Robert MehrabianBorn: 31-Jul-1941Birthplace: Tehran, IranGender: MaleRace or Ethnicity: Middle EasternOccupation: BusinessParty Affiliation: RepublicanNationality: United StatesExecutive summary: CEO of Teledyne    High School: Phillips Exeter Academy    University: BS, Massachusetts Institute of Technology (1964)    University: ScD, Massachusetts Institute of Technology (1968)    Professor: Massachusetts Institute of Technology (1968-75)    Professor: Metallurgy & Mechanical Engineering, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign (1975-79)    Administrator: Dean of Engineering, University of California at Santa Barbara (1983-90)    Administrator: President, Carnegie Mellon University (1990-97)    Teledyne President & CEO (1999-)
    Teledyne EVP (1998-99)
    Teledyne Senior VP Aerospace and Electronics (1997-98)
    National Institute of Standards and Technology Director, Center for Materials Science (1979-83)    Member of the Board of Teledyne Chairman (2000-)
    Member of the Board of Teledyne (1999-)
    Member of the Board of Bank of New York Mellon (2007-)
    Member of the Board of PPG Industries (1992-)
    Member of the Board of Mellon Financial (1994-2007)
    Alcoa Science and Technology Council
    American Society of Metals International Life Member
    Bush-Cheney '04     John McCain 2008     McCain-Palin Victory 2008     National Academy of Engineering     Armenian Ancestry 





